DURBAN  - The Zulu royal household has been allocated R67,316,000 for the 2022/23 financial year. KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala tabled the budget vote at the provincial legislature on Thursday morning. This is the first budget allocated since the recognition of King Misuzulu KaZwelithini as king of the Zulu nation. The soon-to-be-crowned Zulu king has been allocated a budget for the first time. The Zulu royal household receives a budget from the premierâ€™s office each financial year. Premier Sihle Zikalala announced the funds going to the AmaZulu first family. "Royal household is allocated R67,316,000 to support the necessary work that is led by his majesty the king," he said. The money is to assist the king to execute his duties. This also includes annual events such as Umkhosi Welembe, Umkhosi Wamaganu, and Umkhosi Womhlanga. R 67, 316 million has been budgeted for the Zulu Royal Household, this is the first budget since the recognition of King Misuzulu KaZwelithini as King of the Zulu nation. #KZNBudgetVote2022 pic.twitter.com/jNAISUL2KY 